he
is
coming."
"Miss,
you
are
cutting
the
stuff
wrong."
"So
I
am;
but
it
is
only
a
snip.
There
is
no
harm
done."
The
kitchen
door
opened;
Mr.
Moore
entered,
very
wet
and
cold.
Caroline
half
turned
from
her
dressmaking
occupation,
but
renewed
it
for
a
moment,
as
if
to
gain
a
minute's
time
for
some
purpose.
Bent
over
the
dress,
her
face
was
hidden;
there
was
an
attempt
to
settle
her
features
and
veil
their
expression,
which
failed.
When
she
at
last
met
Mr.
Moore,
her
