"But
I
promised
to
return
soon.
You
expected
me,
I
suppose?"
"No,
Robert;
I
dared
not
when
it
rained
so
fast.
And
you
are
wet
and
chilled.
Change
everything.
If
you
took
cold,
I
should
we
should
blame
ourselves
in
some
measure."
"I
am
not
wet
through:
my
riding
coat
is
waterproof.
Dry
shoes
are
all
I
require.
There
the
fire
is
pleasant
after
facing
the
cold
